div.div: Google Forms is an intermediate solution that allows non-technical JAC operations staff to set up tests without help. This will be replaced by Vue App served questions once we have had a chance to iterate on the 'Take a qualifying test' app.

div.style: text-align: left
text-align: left

div.div: Google Apps Scripts collects the users' test answers and sends it as a RESTful call over https to a firebase function, which writes the data to a firestore collection of qualifying test answers. Creation of this record triggers various background functions such as sending confirmation emails and calculating the time a user takes to complete their test.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; max-height: 222px; max-width: 180px; width: 180px; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

div.p: BigQuery is used to collate various entries from Stackdriver logging and feed these as live data to Google Data Studio. This is used to build realtime dashboards. For any given Test we monitor the number of submissions, the number of emails sent and any systemic errors.
